🔍 Introduction to LlamaIndex 

One of the most exciting frontiers in Generative AI today is LlamaIndex is quickly becoming a go-to framework for building these systems.

Traditional LLMs are powerful, but they struggle with factual accuracy, up-to-date knowledge, and context-specific answers. RAG solves this by connecting LLMs with external knowledge sources (databases, APIs, PDFs, or even enterprise documents).

👉 Where LlamaIndex fits in:

•	Provides a structured way to ingest and index data from multiple sources.
•	Build retrieval pipelines so LLMs can query external knowledge efficiently.
•	Supports document loaders, embeddings, and vector stores, making it easy to connect your data with models like GPT or LLaMA.
•	Enables developers to create custom RAG workflows that improve accuracy, transparency, and trustworthiness.

The walkthrough highlights how developers can use LlamaIndex to load, index, query, and evaluate documents—bridging the gap between static LLMs and dynamic, data-aware applications.

✨ With frameworks like this, we’re moving from LLMs as “general chatbots” to domain-expert copilots—grounded in enterprise knowledge, always up-to-date, and far more reliable.
